"'''Goatgrass: The Tale of Ree-Yees'''" is a short story that appeared in the ''[[Tales from Jabba's Palace]]'' anthology, published in January [[1996]] by [[Bantam Spectra]]. It was written by [[Deborah J. Ross|Deborah Wheeler]]. The story provides the backstory of the [[Gran/Legends|Gran]], [[Ree-Yees/Legends|Ree-Yees]] who was present in [[Jabba's Palace/Legends|Jabba's Palace]] in [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]]. The title is a reference to [[Silvergrass|Goatgrass]], a preferred food among Gran.

==Plot summary==
The murderous fugitive [[Ree-Yees/Legends|Ree-Yees]] is secretly cobbling together a [[Bomb/Legends|bomb]] to [[Death/Legends|kill]] [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure/Legends|Jabba]] in return for a full pardon from the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Empire]]. The bomb components come [[Smuggler/Legends|smuggled]] in shipments of [[Silvergrass|Goatgrass]], a [[Foodstuff/Legends|food]] favored by [[Gran/Legends|Gran]]. An encounter with a [[B'omarr Order/Legends|B'omarr monk]] grants Ree-Yees a vision of a fiery future, leading him to believe his bomb will be successful. But his vision presages a different outcome: Ree-Yees has been surgically implanted with a bomb by a distrustful Jabba. During the [[Hutt/Legends|Hutt's]] death throes as he is strangled by [[Princess/Legends|Princess]] [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia]], Jabba activates the device – an [[Explosive charge/Legends|explosion]] rendered redundant by the fiery death of the [[Sail barge/Legends|sail barge]] moments later. 

==Continuity==
''[[Galaxy Guide 5: Return of the Jedi]]'' ([[1990]]), the same roleplaying supplement that provided [[Ree-Yees/Legends|Ree-Yees']] basic backstory as a [[Assassin/Legends|murderer]], suggests that he survived the [[Sail barge/Legends|sail barge]] blast, though this explosives-laden story makes that claim extremely doubtful.<ref name="TERC" />

